<concept id="domain_class">
	<title>Classes</title>

	<prolog>
		<author type="creator">Claude Vedovini</author>

		<metadata>
			<keywords>
				<indexterm>class</indexterm>
				<indexterm>domain</indexterm>
				<indexterm>domain object</indexterm>
			</keywords>
		</metadata>
	</prolog>

	<conbody>
		<p>A class is a representation of a business entity in a domain
			model file. For example, a portfolio management application needs to work with
			business concepts such as portfolios, positions, instruments, and so on, and each of these business concepts may be
			represented by a class.</p>

		<p>A class can be an extension (known as super-class) of an existing
			class.</p>

		<p>A class may not correspond to the exact physical structure of related
			data in a database as it is a business representation.</p>
	</conbody>

